<emphasis id="B9549440FFD1FF9AFF1DF8EF3838F883" bold="true" box="[198,343,1841,1867]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Comments:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="4C2033D1FFD1FF9AFEAFF8EF3BCDF882" authorityName="Louzada &amp; Wanderley" authorityYear="2008" box="[372,674,1841,1866]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Orthophytum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ophiuroides">
<emphasis id="B9549440FFD1FF9AFEAFF8EF3BCDF882" box="[372,674,1841,1866]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Orthophytum ophiuroides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C2033D1FFD1FF9AFCE2F8EF3AA3F882" box="[825,972,1841,1866]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Orthophytum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="navioides">
<emphasis id="B9549440FFD1FF9AFCE2F8EF3AA3F882" box="[825,972,1841,1866]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">O. navioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs from that species by having shorter petals (ca. 1.5 vs. 
<quantity id="4CD8E5B7FFD1FF9AFE12F8863B55F8BA" box="[457,570,1880,1906]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.75" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" unit="cm" value="2.75" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.5">2.5–3 cm</quantity>
) and sepals (ca. 1 vs. 
<quantity id="4CD8E5B7FFD1FF9AFC99F8863AF1F8BA" box="[834,926,1880,1906]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" unit="cm" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3 cm</quantity>
), without glandular trichomes. In addition, the bracts and sepals are red (not green).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9F4852FFD0FF9BFF1DFF46389BFF37" blockId="19.[151,1436,152,371]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
Erroneous identifications of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2033D1FFD0FF9BFDF6FF463A0BFF79" authorityName="Louzada &amp; Wanderley" authorityYear="2008" box="[557,868,152,177]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Orthophytum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ophiuroides">
<emphasis id="B9549440FFD0FF9BFDF6FF463A0BFF79" box="[557,868,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Orthophytum ophiuroides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in herbarium collections are quite common. Vouchers are sometimes identified as 
<taxonomicName id="4C2033D1FFD0FF9BFD87FF613BBEFF10" box="[604,721,191,216]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Orthophytum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="humile">
<emphasis id="B9549440FFD0FF9BFD87FF613BBEFF10" box="[604,721,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">O. humile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but 
<taxonomicName id="4C2033D1FFD0FF9BFCCBFF613AADFF10" authorityName="Louzada &amp; Wanderley" authorityYear="2008" box="[784,962,191,216]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Orthophytum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ophiuroides">
<emphasis id="B9549440FFD0FF9BFCCBFF613AADFF10" box="[784,962,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">O. ophiuroides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has wider and glabrous leaf blades (vs. narrow and densely lepidote).
</paragraph>
